Colombia Stock Movers: Empresa de Telecomunicaciones, Grupo Aval

-- B y   C a m i l a   R u s s o
-- 
2011-03-22T20:38:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-22/colombia-stock-movers-empresa-de-telecomunicaciones-grupo-aval.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index declined 0.3 percent to 14,608.62, while the
Colcap Index rose 0.1 percent to 1,740.98.  Empresa de Telecomunicaciones de Bogota (ETB)  SA dropped
5.5 percent to 656 pesos, the biggest fall since Sept. 6. The
telecommunications provider serving  Colombia ’s capital slid
after Bogota Mayor Samuel Moreno Rojas said the city will
propose the sale of a majority of the company.  Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores (AVAL)  SA fell 5.4 percent
to 1,400 pesos, the steepest drop since November 2008. The
country’s biggest financial holding company will sell between
800 million and 1.6 billion preferential shares with a value of
1,300 pesos each from today to April 11, the company said in a
regulatory filing March 19.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Camila Russo in New York at 
 crusso15@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  